article.description: Jeremiah Martin had 37 points as Memphis narrowly defeated Wichita State 88-85 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Martin scores 37 to carry Memphis over Wichita St. 88-85
article.linkText: Martin scores 37 to carry Memphis over Wichita St. 88-85
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. -- Jeremiah Martin had 37 points as Memphis narrowly defeated Wichita State 88-85 on Saturday night. Martin hit all 14 of his free throw attempts. Raynere Thornton had 16 points and nine rebounds for Memphis (17-11, 9-6 American Athletic Conference). Kareem Brewton Jr. added 14 points. Jaime Echenique had 17 points and 12 rebounds for the Shockers (13-13, 6-8). Dexter Dennis added 17 points. Markis McDuffie had 15 points. The Tigers improve to 2-0 against the Shockers this season. Memphis defeated Wichita State 85-74 on Jan. 3. Memphis faces Temple at home on Tuesday. Wichita State plays Connecticut at home on Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
